  "prompt": "What is the remainder when 676767\u2026 unto 900 digit is divided by 999?",
  "response": "To determine the remainder when the 900-digit number formed by repeating \"67\" is divided by 999, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Construct the Number:**\n   - The number can be represented as \\( N = 676767\\ldots67 \\) with 450 repetitions of \"67,\" resulting in a 900-digit number.\n\n2. **Express \\( N \\) Mathematically:**\n   \\[\n   N = 67 \\times (10^{898} + 10^{896} + \\ldots + 10^2 + 10^0)\n   \\]\n   This can be simplified to:\n   \\[\n   N = 67 \\times \\left(\\sum_{k=0}^{449} 10^{2k}\\right)\n   \\]\n\n3. **Simplify the Sum Modulo 999:**\n   - Note that \\( 10^3 \\equiv 1 \\ (\\text{mod} \\ 999) \\).\n   - The terms \\( 10^{2k} \\) cycle every 3 exponents: \\( 1, 100, 10 \\).\n   - There are 450 terms, which form 150 complete cycles.\n   - Each cycle sums to \\( 1 + 100 + 10 = 111 \\).\n   - Therefore, the total sum is:\n     \\[\n     150 \\times 111 = 16,650\n     \\]\n   - Calculating modulo 999:\n     \\[\n     16,650 \\div 999 = 16 \\ \\text{with a remainder of} \\ 666\n     \\]\n     So, \\( \\sum_{k=0}^{449} 10^{2k} \\equiv 666 \\ (\\text{mod} \\ 999) \\).\n\n4. **Calculate the Final Remainder:**\n   \\[\n   N \\equiv 67 \\times 666 \\ (\\text{mod} \\ 999)\n   \\]\n   - Multiplying:\n     \\[\n     67 \\times 666 = 44,622\n     \\]\n   - Calculating modulo 999:\n     \\[\n     44,622 \\div 999 = 44 \\ \\text{with a remainder of} \\ 666\n     \\]\n     So, \\( N \\equiv 666 \\ (\\text{mod} \\ 999) \\).\n\n**Final Answer:**  \n666",
